Nigerian model, style and brand influencer and entrepreneur, Christiana Kayode, also known as Berbiedoll is one woman who knows how to play her game well. With a beauty that keeps attracting brands and endorsements deals, it is not out of place to say that the TV host has many brands at her beck and call. Speaking with Tribune online in an interview, the TV host, who has operated within the entertainment space for some years said that being a brand influencer goes beyond physical beauty that people see, adding that it is also about adding value to brands and attracting the right audience and giving them value for their money. As a fashion enthusiast and entrepreneur with recognitions from within and outside the country, Berbiedoll, as she’s fondly called, has taken over the landscape of brand and style influencing through her jaw-dropping Instagram posts that keep attracting new followers daily. BOKO HARAM: Candy and pizza for Nigeria’s TERRORISTS FG can’t buy peace through creation of agency for repentant… Nigerian govt is rewarding criminality —Olajide Broken jaws in Jos: When town, gown went to battle over land ALSO READ: Why Nigeria topped bitcoin Google search in 2019 ― Odum Speaking on what has kept her on top of her game, the light-skinned entertainer said her skin is a reflection of her health and nutrients and food that go inside her body daily, adding that “It is important that you pay attention to what you eat so that your living condition would not be hampered by wrong consumption. Berbiedoll who is the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of Berbie Beauty Line, explained how she has managed to remain the delight of many brands, insisting that she does not joke with her sleep and what she eats. “I drink a lot of water and always mind my business, especially the business that pays me. One must exercise daily even if just for half an hour a day and you must have a good night sleep. I don’t joke with that.” The Mass Communications graduate, who also had a brief stint as a video model and appeared in music videos like “Woju” by Kizz Daniel and “Like a Party” by Burna Boy also did a couple of funny video skits with Sydney Talker and Nasty Blaq. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! HERE IS HOW OVER 5000  NIGERIA MEN HAVE PERMANENTLY OVERCOME TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS RECENT DISCOVERY BY MEDICAL CONSULTANTS LOOK!  YOU DONT NEED TO HAVE ANY EXPERIENCE TO TRADE ONLINE,WE WILL DO IT ALL FOR YOU AND YOU WILL START EARNING A LIVING FROM TRADING ONLINE TODAY AND PROFITS WILL BE PAID TO YOUR ACCOUNT DIRECTLY. CLICK HERE TO REGISTER AND EARN